race.comment: GOLD MELODY (1) ran below expectations when hard in the market, finishing seventh over 1258m at Taree. Well placed with the claim and has the ability to find the winners' list. KICKOFF (8) settled well back and never threatened when eighth over 1300m at Taree last time out. Has the class to return to form from the inside gate. CORPSMAN (4) resumes without a trial after finishing ninth over 1450m at Muswellbrook on June 1. Can sprint well fresh despite drawing out. JEVINGTON WILL DO (11) likely to add some value, if he can improve on his Taree performance.
